III_John	1	1	O presbuteros Gaio to agapeto on ego agapo en aletheia
III_John	1	2	Agapete peri panton eukhomai se euodousthai kai ugiainein kathos euodoutai sou e psukhe
III_John	1	3	ekharen gar lian erkhomenon adelphon kai marturounton sou te aletheia kathos su en aletheia peripateis
III_John	1	4	meizoteran touton ouk ekho kharan ina akouo ta ema tekna en te aletheia peripatounta
III_John	1	5	Agapete piston poieis o ean ergase eis tous adelphous kai touto xenous
III_John	1	6	oi emarturesan sou te agape enopion ekklesias ous kalos poieseis propempsas axios tou Theou
III_John	1	7	uper gar tou Onomatos exelthan meden lambanontes apo ton ethnikon
III_John	1	8	emeis oun opheilomen upolambanein tous toioutous ina sunergoi ginometha te aletheia
III_John	1	9	Egrapsa ti te ekklesia all' o philoproteuon auton Diotrephes ouk epidekhetai emas
III_John	1	10	dia touto ean eltho upomneso autou ta erga a poiei logois ponerois phluaron emas kai me arkoumenos epi toutois oute autos epidekhetai tous adelphous kai tous boulomenous koluei kai ek tes ekklesias ekballei
III_John	1	11	Agapete me mimou to kakon alla to agathon o agathopoion ek tou Theou estin o kakopoion oukh eoraken ton Theon
III_John	1	12	Demetrio memarturetai upo panton kai upo autes tes aletheias kai emeis de marturoumen kai oidas oti e marturia emon alethes estin
III_John	1	13	Polla eikhon grapsai soi all' ou thelo dia melanos kai kalamou soi graphein
III_John	1	14	elpizo de eutheos se idein kai stoma pros stoma lalesomen
III_John	1	15	Eirene soi aspazontai se oi philoi aspazou tous philous kat' onoma
